<br>
I'm also wondering if I have an illusion up if my charisma still is effective or will I have the charisma of a plain old skeleton?<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p><p>&nbsp;<p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474342"><img src="http://www.inktank.com/images/eZsig.gif" height=150 width=508 border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqin>eqin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#333333>(1/22/03 9:28:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stein of Mogock faction?</span><hr size=1> Even if you got past the Bouncers, you'd still need enough faction with Clurg for him to hand you the stein.  The chanters can cast &quot;Alliance&quot;? spell to temporarily raise their faction up a notch.  You might try the chanter board for this question, but I don't think you can.<br>
<br>
<br>
I did this quest with my druid, back when Bertox had taken over NK and there was a bread quest in Feerott which enabled me to raise my faction with most of Oggok.<br>
<br>
<br>
Petmeister Ogrepunker<br>
Gnome Magi of the 20th Gear <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=urgathbubblespawner>UrgathBubblespawner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 6:22:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1144.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stein of Mogock faction?</span><hr size=1> I did this for my mage with my 12 chanter alt using Illusion Dark elf (lvl 12 spell) and Alliance.<br>
<br>
I don't know if there's a way to do it for other classes than enc ...<br>
<br>
So since you are on FV I'd suggest you find a chanter friend who does the turn ins while you go buy the nuts and farm the honey thingies ...<br>
<br>
/Urgath <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silverlakes>Silverlakes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/03 9:16:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1144.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stein of Mogock faction?</span><hr size=1> This quest is better doable from chanters since they can use illusions (it avoids u get killed in the different cities) and faction boosts .Charisma doesn't help in the quests. <br>
