<br>
There is an Illusion:Skeleton bracelet and amulet<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=12999">everquest.allakhazam.com/...item=12999</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1143">everquest.allakhazam.com/...?item=1143</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
But it will only get you to indifferent. (plus if you can farm Vex Thal and Fear for these, questing for the stein of moggok is pretty...well...yeah)<br>
<br>
There is also a DE illusion mask that is a bit easier to get:<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1875">everquest.allakhazam.com/...?item=1875</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
It will get you to dubious/apprehensive with most of Oggok, and possibly even indifferent with Clurg.<br>
<br>
Also, at lvl 62, enchanters can get a targeted illusion AA.  Still not a solo effort, but hey.<br>
<br>
I hate to say it can't be done, but it can't be done.  You could multiquest it as far as Freeport, but then an enchanter or Ogre would need to finish the quest and take it to Clurg.  It is faster and safer to level an enchanter up to lvl 12, and do the quest, then swap the stein.  I do this about once a week with my lvl 14 enchanter, and now I can complete the whole quest in about 1/2 an hour (including the regurgitonic quest).  Give the stein to my mage, and let him sell it. <p><DIV style="position:relative; width=80%; filter:Blur(Add = 1, Direction = 225, Strength = 10)">
